<section id="slide-org68ac86c">
<h3 id="org68ac86c"><span class="section-number-3">2.1</span> Conclusions</h3>
<ul>
<li class="fragment appear">A computer is really dumb</li>
<li class="fragment appear">A computer does certain things well, and most things poorly</li>
<li class="fragment appear">A computer is quite basic and low level</li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-orgc18fa2c">
<h3 id="orgc18fa2c"><span class="section-number-3">2.2</span> Computer Architecture</h3>
<ul>
<li class="fragment appear">Differentiation between high level and low level (human to computer)</li>
<li class="fragment appear">Computers understand binary (it's wires)</li>
<li class="fragment appear">We understand English</li>
<li class="fragment appear">English &#x2013;&gt; Python &#x2013;&gt; C &#x2013;&gt; Assembly &#x2013;&gt; Binary</li>

</ul>
