<section>
<section id="slide-org6b98a45">
<h2 id="org6b98a45"><span class="section-number-2">7</span> Control Structures</h2>
<p>
If this, then that
</p>

<ul>
<li class="fragment appear">This is like a fork in the road</li>
<li class="fragment appear">What's a good way to represent whether or not to execute code?  Variable type?</li>
<li class="fragment appear"><p>
Consider
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">

<pre><code class="python" >x, y = 1, 2

if (x < y):
    print('x is less than y')
</code></pre>
</div></li>
<li class="fragment appear">When will it execute the print statement?</li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-orgdfb8a96">
<h3 id="orgdfb8a96"><span class="section-number-3">7.1</span> If, elif, and else</h3>
<ul>
<li class="fragment appear"><p>
What's the difference here, is there one?
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">

<pre><code class="python" >x, y = 1, 2

if (x < y):
    print ('x is less than y')

if (x < y):
    print ('Yipee')

if (x > y):
    print('Nope')
</code></pre>
</div>
<div class="org-src-container">

<pre><code class="python" >x, y = 1, 2

if (x < y):
    print('x is less than y')

elif (x < y):
    print('Yipee')

else:
    print('Nope')
</code></pre>
</div></li>

</ul>
